                        Fronttalk Defines:  WELLMSG

Usage:  DEFINE WELLMSG "<string>"

The WELLMSG define is used to generate the output from the "DISPLAY WELCOME"
command.  (Note that the LINMSG also displays the welcome file.)

For full details on its format, see help pages on SEPARATORS, CONFFUNC,
CONFCOND, and SEPDATE.

The default value is:

   "%(1x%4g%)%c"
